08:16.713 --> 08:17.845
[Wood clatters]

08:17.888 --> 08:19.716
[Intruder groaning]

08:30.335 --> 08:32.947
[Grunts, groans]

08:37.865 --> 08:40.693
Another time, another place,
a man tried to kill me,

08:40.780 --> 08:43.044
I would've shot him or
thrown him out of a window

08:43.131 --> 08:45.089
and forgotten
he ever existed.

08:45.176 --> 08:46.961
But I'm older now.

08:47.048 --> 08:49.137
And mostly wiser.

08:49.224 --> 08:50.530
Do you have a name?

08:52.619 --> 08:54.316
Didn't think so.

08:57.275 --> 09:00.670
Are you a Dean Martin fan?

09:00.801 --> 09:02.367
I figure that you've
been well-trained

09:02.498 --> 09:04.587
and won't be easily
persuaded to talk,

09:04.718 --> 09:06.415
but I'm gonna ask you
some questions, anyway.

09:06.546 --> 09:09.026
Easy questions. And
every time you don't answer

09:09.200 --> 09:10.550
or say, "Je sais pas,"

09:10.637 --> 09:12.247
I'm gonna kick you
in the head.

09:12.377 --> 09:13.901
You know? Like the song?

09:13.988 --> 09:16.207
And then answer
the question myself.

09:16.338 --> 09:17.731
Sound good?

09:17.818 --> 09:19.733
[Blow lands, man grunts]

09:19.863 --> 09:21.691
Off we go.

09:21.778 --> 09:23.388
So I don't have to
be J. Edgar Hoover

09:23.519 --> 09:26.391
to guess that you're
army intelligence

09:26.522 --> 09:28.829
and that your employers
at SDECE --

09:28.959 --> 09:30.744
Did I pronounce that
right?

09:30.874 --> 09:32.310
[Blow lands]

09:32.397 --> 09:34.704
[Speaking French]

09:34.835 --> 09:37.272
That's always been
a hard one for me.

09:37.402 --> 09:40.101
Where was I? Oh, yeah.
SDECE, army intelligence,

09:40.188 --> 09:42.059
the outfit that you work for,

09:42.146 --> 09:44.801
who I'm assuming, like everyone
else in the known universe,

09:44.888 --> 09:47.456
is angry with
Philippe Saint-Andre

09:47.543 --> 09:49.284
for stealing something,

09:49.327 --> 09:52.809
or, in this case, someone,
he was ordered to protect.

09:53.331 --> 09:55.464
No, that wasn't a question.

09:55.507 --> 09:58.989
But Sergeant Saint-Andre does
work for SDECE, doesn't he?

09:59.120 --> 10:00.730
[Blow lands, man grunts]

10:00.774 --> 10:03.864
That wasa question,
and the answer is...

10:03.951 --> 10:05.953
[Speaking French]

10:08.608 --> 10:10.305
But he went rogue.

10:13.525 --> 10:15.789
So did you and your pal
drop by tonight

10:15.876 --> 10:19.314
to see if the girl could
tell you where the kid is?

10:19.357 --> 10:21.229
[Blow lands, man grunts]

10:21.272 --> 10:23.187
[Speaking French]

10:23.318 --> 10:24.972
Because
the original likely plan

10:25.102 --> 10:27.801
was that Sergeant Saint-Andre
was to deliver the kid

10:27.888 --> 10:29.933
to the big boys in Paris.

10:30.020 --> 10:31.805
[Blow lands]

10:33.937 --> 10:36.853
[Speaking French]

10:36.940 --> 10:40.727
I'm on a hot streak, but now
for the million-franc question.

10:40.857 --> 10:44.948
What is so important
about this little kid

10:45.079 --> 10:47.777
that everyone is
willing to murder nuns

10:47.864 --> 10:52.260
or kidnap young girls in order
to get their hands on him?

10:52.347 --> 10:53.391
I don't know.

10:53.478 --> 10:55.829
Orders were come and search,

10:55.959 --> 11:00.747
and if the boy wasn't
there, to take the girl.

11:00.834 --> 11:03.619
But you came dressed
for war,

11:03.706 --> 11:08.493
all gunned up like you thought
you might get into a firefight.

11:08.537 --> 11:09.843
You have a reputation.

11:09.930 --> 11:11.322
I'm flattered, but...

11:11.453 --> 11:13.194
[Blow lands]

11:14.761 --> 11:18.068
Please, stop doing that.

11:18.155 --> 11:20.070
I will if you stop
talking bullshit.

11:20.157 --> 11:22.856
You thought Philippe
might be here.

11:22.943 --> 11:24.988
For good reason.

11:25.032 --> 11:28.557
Do you know what
Saint-Andre did in Algeria?

11:28.600 --> 11:30.298
He was with a sniper unit.

11:30.385 --> 11:32.343
A secret spy unit.

11:32.430 --> 11:36.826
Saint-Andre hunted down members
of Organisation Armée Secrète.

11:36.913 --> 11:39.307
Yes.
And assassinated them.

11:39.394 --> 11:41.048
He had over 30 kills.

11:41.091 --> 11:43.354
Still, that tells me
nothing as to why everyone,

11:43.398 --> 11:46.836
from the Vatican, to French
intelligence, to the CIA,

11:46.880 --> 11:48.708
is after this kid.

11:48.751 --> 11:51.145
All I know is what
I have heard whispered.

11:51.275 --> 11:55.671
Okay,
then whisper it to me.

11:59.196 --> 12:03.766
That the boy is the hub
of a many-spoked wheel.

12:04.811 --> 12:08.162
That sounds like something
you'd read in a fortune cookie.

12:08.249 --> 12:10.904
It's all I've heard.

12:10.991 --> 12:12.906
I swear on my mother's life.

12:15.996 --> 12:17.301
Okay.

12:19.739 --> 12:21.305
You can go now
and meet your pal,

12:21.479 --> 12:23.177
who's probably
outside somewhere,

12:23.264 --> 12:25.570
bleeding on my grapes.

12:30.575 --> 12:34.057
Really?
I can go?

12:34.188 --> 12:36.799
You tell whoever gave
you this shit detail

12:36.930 --> 12:38.758
that I would like to
find the good sergeant

12:38.845 --> 12:40.194
as much as they would,

12:40.281 --> 12:42.196
if for no other reason
than the bata

12:42.283 --> 12:44.720
has spoiled
my fucking tranquility,

12:44.807 --> 12:48.071
and that when I find Philippe --
and I will find him --

12:48.158 --> 12:51.640
I will talk to him, and then I
will bundle him up in a carpet

12:51.771 --> 12:53.381
and send him up to Paris
for you guys

12:53.468 --> 12:55.122
to do
whatever you want with.

12:55.209 --> 12:58.516
But in the meantime,
if I catch any more armed men

12:58.603 --> 13:01.868
in their jammies sneaking
about my property,

13:01.955 --> 13:05.175
I will shoot them
in the balls.

13:12.879 --> 13:15.403
I wasn't lying before.

13:15.490 --> 13:18.754
We know who you are.

13:18.798 --> 13:22.192
You say that
as if I'm hiding.

13:22.236 --> 13:24.760
You have many enemies.

13:24.847 --> 13:26.718
Okay,
so I'm sending you away

13:26.762 --> 13:29.896
with a few dents in your face
after you tried to kill me,

13:30.026 --> 13:33.160
and now you wanna stand
there and threaten me?

13:33.247 --> 13:36.119
My good friend, you wanna
advertise my whereabouts

13:36.250 --> 13:37.860
in the morning Le Monde

13:37.991 --> 13:41.951
or one night on
Discorama,be my guest.

13:42.082 --> 13:47.827
But you will find that no one
cares about that Sam Spade.

13:47.870 --> 13:49.480
Not anymore.

13:49.567 --> 13:51.004
[Tense music plays]

13:51.091 --> 13:54.485
You tell your bosses
we're not enemies.

13:54.572 --> 13:56.792
And they should believe you?

13:56.879 --> 13:58.446
Why?

