20:49.813 --> 20:51.554
Cynthia: George and I
had just sat down

20:51.685 --> 20:53.252
to do The Timescryptic

20:53.295 --> 20:55.428
when we heard
your man shouting.

20:55.471 --> 20:57.517
You could hear him
from your place?

20:57.604 --> 20:59.475
Well, we were
in the garden.

20:59.519 --> 21:01.999
The fresh air being part
of our daily ritual.

21:02.130 --> 21:04.611
That, and the, uh, mimosas,
of course.

21:04.698 --> 21:08.136
Here's a possible theory --
In trying to make his escape,

21:08.179 --> 21:11.922
this chap runs
this way and tumbles in.

21:12.009 --> 21:13.446
That's
my considered opinion.

21:13.489 --> 21:15.404
Might wanna reconsider
that opinion.

21:15.491 --> 21:17.450
The road
is the other direction.

21:17.537 --> 21:19.930
No moon last night.
Darkness aplenty.

21:20.017 --> 21:22.019
He's not familiar
with the terrain, so...

21:22.106 --> 21:25.109
Still, one doesn't die from
simply tumbling into the pool.

21:25.196 --> 21:28.417
One does if one can't swim.He was a trained commando.

21:28.504 --> 21:30.114
Who was also
bleeding to death.

21:30.201 --> 21:31.290
I only winged him.

21:34.162 --> 21:35.990
[Speaking French]

21:41.735 --> 21:44.390
[Conversing in French]

22:02.103 --> 22:04.758
His partner didn't escape.
I let him go.

22:04.845 --> 22:08.327
I didn't see much point
in hanging onto him.

22:08.414 --> 22:09.893
In the same way there
wasn't much point

22:09.937 --> 22:11.721
when I saw you this morning
in telling me

22:11.852 --> 22:14.637
that two men had tried
to kidnap Teresa?

22:14.724 --> 22:16.465
In my experience,
the fewer people know

22:16.509 --> 22:18.946
about something like this,
the fewer people get hurt.

22:19.033 --> 22:22.863
Your concern for
my well-being is most touching.

22:22.993 --> 22:24.691
A difficult shot in daylight.

22:24.821 --> 22:28.477
This was at night, which makes
such precision impossible.

22:28.564 --> 22:30.610
Not if one had
a night-vision scope,

22:30.697 --> 22:32.263
like the PV-1 Starlight.

22:32.351 --> 22:33.656
That would do the trick.

22:33.743 --> 22:36.180
George was in
the Royal Fusiliers.

22:36.267 --> 22:38.008
Is that where he
learned to paint?

22:38.095 --> 22:39.706
Were you a rifleman?

22:39.749 --> 22:40.707
Typing pool.

22:40.794 --> 22:42.404
Yeah. Tepid shot.

22:42.535 --> 22:44.014
I bet you are.

22:44.101 --> 22:46.887
Henri, I suggest
you call the base

22:46.930 --> 22:48.889
and let them deal
with the body.

22:48.976 --> 22:51.848
General Davou is a man
who insists on boundaries.

22:51.935 --> 22:54.024
The soldier's his.But the pool is mine.

22:54.111 --> 22:56.723
This problem comes from
inside their own house.

22:58.899 --> 23:00.379
Thank you for your time.

23:00.509 --> 23:04.470
